OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1779358003
OL,3,CHealth warning issued ahead of
OL,4,Canticipated Bank Holiday heatwave
OL,6,FIn a welcome break from tradition, the
OL,7,Fweather is promising to be warm and
OL,8,Fsunny across the UK this Bank Holiday
OL,9,Fweekend and into half-term week.
OL,11,FIn fact, the likelihood of some areas
OL,12,Fseeing their first heatwave of the
OL,13,Fyear is increasing, with the UK Health
OL,14,FSecurity Agency (UKHSA) issuing a heat
OL,15,Fhealth alert for several regions in
OL,16,FEngland from Friday.
OL,18,FHow hot is it going to get, and where
OL,19,Fwill be hottest?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1779358003
OL,3,CHealth warning issued ahead of
OL,4,Canticipated Bank Holiday heatwave
OL,6,FTemperatures will rise steadily over
OL,7,Fthe next few days, with many areas
OL,8,Fbecoming very warm or even hot by the
OL,9,Fweekend.
OL,11,FThe hottest temperatures will be
OL,12,Frecorded across southern and central
OL,13,FEngland, parts of Wales and sheltered
OL,14,Finland areas away from the coast.
OL,16,FMaximum temperatures could hit 30C in
OL,17,Fthe southeast over the Bank Holiday
OL,18,Fweekend.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1779358003
OL,3,CHealth warning issued ahead of
OL,4,Canticipated Bank Holiday heatwave
OL,6,FNot quite as hot elsewhere, but
OL,7,Ftemperatures are still expected to
OL,8,Fsoar well above the seasonal average;
OL,9,Fwidely 17-23C in the north, and 24-30C
OL,10,Fin the south.
OL,12,FActually, with high pressure expected
OL,13,Fto dominate the picture into next
OL,14,Fweek, fine weather is likely to
OL,15,Fcontinue for most places throughout,
OL,16,Fwhich is, for many, half-term week.
OL,18,FSome patchy rain may affect the far
OL,19,Fnorth at times, and perhaps a few
OL,20,Fshowers in the far south, but it will
OL,21,Fremain warm or very warm.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
