PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1779358003
OL,3,CHealth warning issued ahead of
OL,4,Canticipated Bank Holiday heatwave
OL,6,FWhere has a heat-health alert been
OL,7,Fissued, and what does that actually
OL,8,Fmean?
OL,10,FThe UKHSA and the Met Office have
OL,11,Fissued a yellow heat-health alert
OL,12,Fcovering London, the South East, East
OL,13,Fof England and both the East and West
OL,14,FMidlands from Friday, May 22, until
OL,15,FWednesday, May 27.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1779358003
OL,3,CHealth warning issued ahead of
OL,4,Canticipated Bank Holiday heatwave
OL,6,FThe Heat-Health Alert system is
OL,7,Fdesigned to warn health and care
OL,8,Fservices about weather conditions that
OL,9,Fcould affect vulnerable people,
OL,10,Fparticularly older people and those
OL,11,Fwith underlying health conditions.
OL,13,FCould this become an official heatwave?
OL,15,FIt's certainly becoming a strong
OL,16,Fpossibility. The Met Office definition
OL,17,Fof a heatwave is three consecutive
OL,18,Fdays where temperatures meet or exceed
OL,19,Fa specific threshold for that county.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1779358003
OL,3,CHealth warning issued ahead of
OL,4,Canticipated Bank Holiday heatwave
OL,6,FThose thresholds vary across the UK
OL,7,Fbut, broadly speaking, are around 25C
OL,8,Facross the north and west of the UK
OL,9,Fand around 28C in London and the
OL,10,Fsoutheast.
OL,12,FWith temperatures expected to remain
OL,13,Fvery elevated for several days in
OL,14,Fsouthern England, some areas here
OL,15,Fcould potentially meet that official
OL,16,Fheatwave criteria, resulting in the
OL,17,Ffirst heatwave of the year.
OL,19,FWill it stay sunny everywhere?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1779358003
OL,3,CHealth warning issued ahead of
OL,4,Canticipated Bank Holiday heatwave
OL,6,FMostly - but not completely. As we so
OL,7,Foften see, as temperatures and
OL,8,Fhumidity rise, so too does the risk of
OL,9,Fheavy, thundery showers - and it's
OL,10,Fvery possible some areas will see
OL,11,Fthese isolated downpours over the
OL,12,Fweekend.
OL,14,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,15,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,16,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,17,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
